track_notes: This is a nice forest walk to the summit. You can park at the village. the way dwown i used is a forest road. the valley is fine and summit is ok to set up antenna.
This time i used my Mountain bike to reach the summit; used the forest road until the crest, then finished walking by feet. Nice when you get down!

Mostly the same track as i used 10 years before! As the way down is a bit silly, you can use the way up for returning to the car. You can park in the village Le Moulinet; the sloop is a bit hard but the path is very good. The sight is fine and you can see the Corsica Island when sky is clear.
